The Lagos State House of Assembly Service Commission (LAHASCOM) has appointed Ms Abosede Lambo as its Executive Secretary. The announcement was contained in a letter on Saturday by the commission’s Chairman, Wale Mogaji. It said Lambo’s appointment was in line with the provision of Section 8 Subsection 1 of LAHASCOM Act and a correspondence marked LSHASC/AD/O/201/71 from the House of Assembly. Mogaji stated that the appointment was with effect from Thursday, February 13, 2020. He noted that the selection was a reflection of Lambo’s “commitment and selfless service to the State and the Legislative Service in particular”. The commission said it looked forward to the new secretary’s “dedication and demonstration of integrity in the discharge of duties”. The new ES joined the Lagos State Public Service in February 1990 as an Information Officer and later rose to become a director.